race.comment: RUSTENBURG (1) may have suffered from the dreaded second-up syndrome last time out but the two runner-up finishes to start the career were full of merit. Will be ready to peak now third-up from the spell and gets some weight off with the 2kg claim. Expected to take some running down. GAS BRIGADE (18) resumes here but has revved up for this with two recent trials and must be respected out of the Heathcote yard. Can run a race while fresh. MISSISSIPPI DREAM (11) gets the reliable Vandyke/Maloney combination and shapes as one of the main hopes. ELROND (8) has placed two from two over this course and distance and looks a must for the multiples. DIOSA (10) brings Victorian form to the table and any market push must be noted.
